[32m+[m[32m# Copilot Instructions for Stavbe Codebase[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Overview[m
[32m+[m[32mThis repository is a full-stack solution for managing building (stavbe) data, with a .NET API backend and an Angular client frontend. The workspace is organized into two main folders: `API/` (C#/.NET) and `client/` (Angular). Data flows from the backend (Entity Framework, REST controllers) to the frontend (Angular services/components).[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Key Architectural Patterns[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Backend (API/):**[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Uses Entity Framework Core for data access (`Data/`, `Entities/`, `Migrations/`).[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Business logic and data queries are in `Data/Repos/` (e.g., `MojElektroRepository.cs`).[m
[32m+[m[32m  - DTOs in `DTOs/` are used for shaping API responses.[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Controllers in `Controllers/` expose REST endpoints.[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Helpers, middleware, and extensions are in their respective folders for cross-cutting concerns.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Frontend (client/):**[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Angular 18+ project structure (`src/app/`).[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Models in `_models/` mirror backend DTOs/entities for type safety.[m
[32m+[m[32m  - UI logic is split into feature modules/components (e.g., `moj-elektro-card`).[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Uses `ngx-bootstrap` for UI widgets (e.g., datepickers/tabs).[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Developer Workflows[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Build/Run:**[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Backend: Use Visual Studio or `dotnet build`, run with `dotnet run`.[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Frontend: Use `ng serve` for development, `ng build` for production builds.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Testing:**[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Backend: Standard .NET test projects (not present in context, add if needed).[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Frontend: Run `ng test` for unit tests (Karma).[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Debugging:**[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Backend: Use Visual Studio debugger or `dotnet watch run`.[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Frontend: Use browser dev tools and Angular CLI error output.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Project-Specific Conventions[m
[32m+[m[32m- **DTOs and Entities:**[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Always use DTOs for API responses; do not expose entities directly.[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Map entities to DTOs using AutoMapper (see `Helpers/AutoMapperProfiles.cs`).[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Repository Pattern:**[m
[32m+[m[32m  - All data access is via repository classes in `Data/Repos/`.[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Async methods return `Task<T>` and use EF Core's async LINQ methods.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Frontend Data Binding:**[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Use Angular's async pipes and RxJS for API calls.[m
[32m+[m[32m  - UI components expect strongly typed models from `_models/`.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **UI Libraries:**[m
[32m+[m[32m  - For datepickers/tabs, import `ngx-bootstrap` modules in your Angular module (see error troubleshooting above).[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Integration Points[m
[32m+[m[32m- **API <-> Client:**[m
[32m+[m[32m  - REST endpoints in `Controllers/` are consumed by Angular services.[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Data contracts are kept in sync via DTOs and TypeScript interfaces.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **External Dependencies:**[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Angular: `ngx-bootstrap`, `@types/google.maps` (for map features).[m
[32m+[m[32m  - API: Entity Framework Core, AutoMapper.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Examples[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Adding a new API endpoint:**[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Create a DTO in `DTOs/`, update the entity in `Entities/`, add logic in `Data/Repos/`, expose via a controller in `Controllers/`.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Adding a new Angular feature:**[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Generate a component (`ng generate component`), add a model in `_models/`, create a service for API calls, and update routing/module as needed.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Key Files/Folders[m
[32m+[m[32m- `API/Controllers/` - REST API endpoints[m
[32m+[m[32m- `API/Data/Repos/` - Data access logic[m
[32m+[m[32m- `API/DTOs/` - Data transfer objects[m
[32m+[m[32m- `client/src/app/_models/` - TypeScript models[m
[32m+[m[32m- `client/src/app/` - Angular components/services[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIf any section is unclear or missing important project-specific details, please provide feedback or specify which workflows/patterns need more documentation.[m
